<LP>
   BOISE CASCADE Corp., Boise, Idaho, announced a public
offering of $125 million of 9.85% notes due in 2002. The
offering was largely sold at the time of pricing yesterday,
the company said. The forest products company said the
proceeds will go toward repayment of short-term debt and
general corporate purposes. The underwriters are First Boston
Corp., Goldman, Sachs &amp; Co., Lazard Freres &amp; Co. and Salomon
Brothers Inc.
