</IN>
<LP>
   Boots Co. and W.H. Smith Group PLC announced a joint
venture in Britain's do-it-yourself market that will create a
company to own and manage both British retailers'
home-improvement stores.
   Boots and W.H. Smith will each own 50% of the venture,
which will have net assets of #104 million ($174.3 million)
