million hostile bid for Ward White Group PLC, a diversified
stores and manufacturing group, had pretax profit of #8.7
million on sales of #273 million in the 14 months ended March
31. Do It All had pretax profit of #7.7 million on sales of
#238 million in the year ended June 3, 1989.
   "This is a major realignment in the {do-it-yourself}
market," said Malcolm Field, group managing director of W.H.
Smith and chairman of the joint-venture company. He said the
companies "believe that this market has considerable scope
for profitable growth."
