06/06/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B2
</SO>
<CO>
   UAL
</CO>
<IN>
AIRLINES (AIR)
</IN>
<LP>
   CHICAGO -- United Airlines, a unit of UAL Corp., said its
May traffic rose 7.9% to 6.05 billion revenue passenger miles
from 5.6 billion miles a year earlier. A revenue passenger
mile is one paying passsenger flown one mile.
   The carrier's May load factor, or the percentage of
available seats occupied, rose to 63.4% from 62.6%.
</LP>
