<HL>
   International Brief -- Argyll Group PLC:
   Fiscal 1990 Pretax Profit
   Rose 27% to $381.2 Million
</HL>
<DATE>
06/06/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   U.AYL
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Argyll Group PLC, a British food and drink retailer, said
pretax profit for the year ended March 31 rose 27% to #227.5
million ($381.2 million) from #178.7 million a year earlier,
citing big gains from its Safeway supermarket chain --
formerly part of the U.S. chain but now unrelated.
   Profit after taxes but before special items also rose 27%
to #159.2 million from #125.1 million. Per-share earnings
rose 25% to 17.2 pence from 13.8 pence. Profit attributable
to shareholders rose 30% to #163.3 million from #125.1
million, boosted by a #4.1 million gain from proceeds from an
asset sale; the year-earlier period didn't have any special
items.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Sales increased 12% to #4.1 billion from #3.7 billion.
   Operating profit rose 20% to #224.6 million from #187.8
million. Argyll said Safeway contributed 68% of total sales
and 71% of operating profit. Safeway sales increased 35% to
#2.8 billion and operating profit rose 50% to #158.8 million.
   The company proposed a final dividend of 4.80 pence,
making the total payout for the year 7.25 pence, up 17% from
6.20 pence a year earlier.
</TEXT>
