   Business Brief -- Horizon Healthcare Corp.:
   Mortgages, Loan Refinanced
   With a New Lead Lender
</HL>
<DATE>
06/06/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   HHC
</CO>
<LP>
   Horizon Healthcare Corp. said it refinanced about $20
million in mortgages and an $8 million working-capital loan
with a new lead lender at lower interest rates.
   The Albuquerque, N.M.-based owner of nursing homes and
retirement facilities said its new mortgage and credit
agreement is led by HomeFed Bank of San Diego and carries an
interest rate 1 1/2 percentage points above the prime rate.
</LP>
